      <title>Episode 10: F# and Functional Programming</title>
      <link>https://unhandledexceptionpodcast.com/posts/0010-fsharp/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 24 Jan 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://unhandledexceptionpodcast.com/posts/0010-fsharp/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In this group episode I was joined by &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/ScottWlaschin&#34;&gt;Scott Wlaschin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/isaac_abraham&#34;&gt;Isaac Abraham&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/ijrussell&#34;&gt;Ian Russell&lt;/a&gt; - to talk all about F#! This is .NET&amp;rsquo;s functional programming language, and we discussed functional programming, and the benefits of using a functional programming language like F#, whilst also comparing it to other languages like C#.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div id=&#34;buzzsprout-player-7454740&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;script src=&#34;https://www.buzzsprout.com/978640/7454740-hello-world.js?container_id=buzzsprout-player-7454740&amp;player=small&#34; type=&#34;text/javascript&#34; charset=&#34;utf-8&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;guests-social-links&#34;&gt;Guests&amp;rsquo; social links&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Ian Russell: &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/ijrussell&#34;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.linkedin.com/in/ian-russell-7b5301ba/&#34;&gt;LinkedIn&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Isaac Abraham: &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/isaac_abraham&#34;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.linkedin.com/in/isaacabraham/&#34;&gt;LinkedIn&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Scott Wlaschin: &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/ScottWlaschin&#34;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.linkedin.com/in/scottwlaschin/&#34;&gt;LinkedIn&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;links-from-the-show&#34;&gt;Links from the show&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://fsharpforfunandprofit.com/&#34;&gt;F# for fun and profit&lt;/a&gt; (Scott&amp;rsquo;s website)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.softwarepark.cc/blog/2020/8/9/introduction-to-functional-programming-in-f-table-of-contents&#34;&gt;Ian&amp;rsquo;s &amp;ldquo;Introduction To Functional Programming In F#&amp;rdquo; blog post series&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.manning.com/books/get-programming-with-f-sharp&#34;&gt;Isaac&amp;rsquo;s book: &amp;ldquo;Get Programming with F#&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://fsharpforfunandprofit.com/books/&#34;&gt;Scott&amp;rsquo;s book: &amp;ldquo;Domain Modeling Made Functional&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.danclarke.com/2020-more-succinct-csharp&#34;&gt;Dan&amp;rsquo;s &amp;ldquo;Writing More Succinct C#&amp;rdquo; blog post&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/dracan/status/1260942493878804481&#34;&gt;C# code-snippet Dan referred to when talking about using LINQ on a single object&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://nancyfx.org/&#34;&gt;Nancy Framework&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/CarterCommunity/Carter&#34;&gt;Carter&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/ardalis/ApiEndpoints&#34;&gt;API Endpoints&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Diamond Kata:&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.natpryce.com/articles/000807.html&#34;&gt;Diamond Kata - TDD with only property-based tests&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://blog.ploeh.dk/2015/01/10/diamond-kata-with-fscheck&#34;&gt;Diamond Kata in F#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.apress.com/gb/book/9781484239995&#34;&gt;Book: &amp;ldquo;Stylish F#&amp;rdquo; by Kit Eason&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/kitlovesfsharp&#34;&gt;@kitlovesfsharp&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://fsharpforfunandprofit.com/posts/ten-reasons-not-to-use-a-functional-programming-language/&#34;&gt;Blog post: &amp;ldquo;Ten reasons not to use a statically typed functional programming language&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Like most programmers, Iâ€™m naturally conservative and I dislike learning new things. That&amp;rsquo;s why I picked a career in IT.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt; is from this post)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B06Y649387&#34;&gt;&amp;ldquo;Why We Sleep&amp;rdquo; book&lt;/a&gt; (from one of the dev-tips)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;links-related-to-the-topics-we-discussed&#34;&gt;Links related to the topics we discussed&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Composition:&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oquuPOkz8xo&#34;&gt;Video: &amp;ldquo;The Power of Composition&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt; - explains piping and other composition techniques&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://fsharpforfunandprofit.com/rop/&#34;&gt;Video and blog: &amp;ldquo;Railway oriented programming&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt; - shows some composition techniques for error handling&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Property Based Testing:&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://fsharpforfunandprofit.com/posts/property-based-testing/&#34;&gt;Blog post: An introduction to property-based testing&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IYzDFHx6QPY&#34;&gt;Video: The lazy programmer&amp;rsquo;s guide to writing thousands of tests&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Functional architecture:&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=USSkidmaS6w&#34;&gt;Video: &amp;ldquo;Reinventing the Transaction Script&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt; - talks about pushing I/O to the edges&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=US8QG9I1XW0&#34;&gt;Video: &amp;ldquo;Functional architecture - The pits of success - Mark Seemann&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://fsharpforfunandprofit.com/posts/cyclic-dependencies/&#34;&gt;Blog post: &amp;ldquo;Cyclic dependencies are evil&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PLFl95c-IiU&#34;&gt;Video: &amp;ldquo;Domain Modeling Made Functional&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KPa8Yw_Navkd&#34;&gt;Video: &amp;ldquo;F# for C# Programmers&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MGLxyyTF3OM&#34;&gt;Video: &amp;ldquo;F# Code I love&amp;rdquo; by Don Syme&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.compositional-it.com/news-blog/tag/fp-on-net-series/&#34;&gt;Isaac&amp;rsquo;s &amp;ldquo;FP on .NET&amp;rdquo; blog post series&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;f-community-and-other-links&#34;&gt;F# Community and other links&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://fsharp.org/guides/slack/&#34;&gt;Join the F# slack&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/search?q=%23fsharp&amp;amp;f=live&#34;&gt;F# hashtag on twitter&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://sergeytihon.com/&#34;&gt;F# Weekly - A roundup of F# content from each week&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/fsprojects/awesome-fsharp&#34;&gt;Awesome F# - list of libraries, links and resources&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Episode 9: Functional Programming in C# with Simon Painter</title>
      <link>https://unhandledexceptionpodcast.com/posts/0009-simonpainter/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 03 Jan 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://unhandledexceptionpodcast.com/posts/0009-simonpainter/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;For this very first episode of 2021, I was joined by &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.twitter.com/madSimonJ&#34;&gt;Simon Painter&lt;/a&gt; to talk all about Functional Programming in C#! We spoke about functional concepts, plus terms such as &lt;em&gt;Options&lt;/em&gt;, &lt;em&gt;Maybes&lt;/em&gt;, and even tried to explain what a Monad is! As usual, there were a few tangents, and we also touched on topics such as React, TDD, and much more!&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div id=&#34;buzzsprout-player-7108510&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;script src=&#34;https://www.buzzsprout.com/978640/7108510-hello-world.js?container_id=buzzsprout-player-7108510&amp;player=small&#34; type=&#34;text/javascript&#34; charset=&#34;utf-8&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;links-from-the-show&#34;&gt;Links from the show&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Simon&amp;rsquo;s social links:&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.twitter.com/madSimonJ&#34;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.thecodepainter.co.uk/&#34;&gt;Website&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.manning.com/books/functional-programming-in-c-sharp&#34;&gt;Book: Functional Programming in C# by Enrico Buonanno&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v7WLC5As6g4&#34;&gt;Recording of Simon&amp;rsquo;s &amp;lsquo;Functional Programming in C# talk&lt;/a&gt; (thanks to &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.meetup.com/dotnetsheff/&#34;&gt;.NET Sheff&lt;/a&gt; for this, as we didn&amp;rsquo;t record his talk at .NET Oxford)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://vimeo.com/97344498&#34;&gt;Scott Wlaschin - Railway Oriented Programming video&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://ramdajs.com/&#34;&gt;Ramda JS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.danclarke.com/2020-more-succinct-csharp&#34;&gt;Dan&amp;rsquo;s &amp;lsquo;Writing More Succinct C#&amp;rsquo; blog post&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://reactjs.org/&#34;&gt;React&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://dotnet.microsoft.com/apps/machinelearning-ai/ml-dotnet&#34;&gt;ML.NET&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;DevTip links&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://apps.ankiweb.net/&#34;&gt;Anki&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://regex101.com/&#34;&gt;regex101.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://darklang.com/&#34;&gt;Darklang&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
